oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Cockatiels
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: DeWald, Dale David
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Fast flying and long-lived, Australiancockatiels have become world-wide petfavorites. Almost every cockatiel sold inthe United States has been raised in captivity,but the demand is so great thatmany of these fine birds are importedfrom breeders in other countries. Cockatielsare social birds that also requirequiet times. They are easy to tame andwill enjoy a few hours out of their cagewith their master each day. In generalthey are not great talkers, but most canbe taught a few simple whistles andmany are very good talkers. If you donot train your pet as a companionanimal, please procure a second bird tomeet the social requirements of theseavian delights.
